The paper deals with head pose estimation using a convolutional neural network trained on a large dataset. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of a neural network for pose estimation suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions testing on benchmark datasets, which suggests multimedia (cs.MM) as a possible category. Finally, the applications of head pose estimation mentioned in the abstract, such as gaze estimation and face alignment, suggest human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as another possible category.
